d=\"1a04a2d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-73eb6eb\" data-id=\"73eb6eb\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ac855f7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ac855f7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Lori was first licensed as a real estate agent in Sacramento, California in 1990, where she worked the residential market for two years. However, she soon became intrigued by the complexities of investing in and developing rural land and took on her first project. Since then, she\u2019s had over twenty years of experience in real estate markets in three states, mainly buying and selling rural properties for investment purposes. More recently, she\u2019s become a licensed Realtor\u00ae&#8211;first in Texas, then New Mexico\u2014and has enjoyed the real estate opportunities that keep her busy in both states. Lori is also a member of both the national REALTORS\u00ae Land Institute (RLI) and the Texas Alliance of Land Brokers (TALB). In central Texas, Lori has enjoyed the challenge of helping relocation clients, and serving the traditional needs of Buyers and Sellers. In order to better serve client needs, she\u2019s a member of three MLS systems: Four Rivers Association of Realtors\u00ae (FRAR), Austin Board of Realtors\u00ae (ABOR) and San Antonio Board of Realtors\u00ae (SABOR). She considers it a real privilege to participate in achieving the goals of her clients, and every transaction is measured in terms of the friendships formed.<\/p>\n<p>Background:<br>Lori and her husband, Don, grew up and married near Vancouver, Canada, then emigrated to California, where they were blessed with three daughters over the years. In 2004, she graduated summa cum laude, Phi Kappa Phi, with a B.A. in Communications from CA State University, Sacramento. In 2005, their family moved to the Texas Hill Country\u2014for two years in west Austin, then to acreage outside San Marcos. Don (CPA, MBA) retired several years ago from his work as an institutional money manager, and now contributes an unusual mix of business acumen, marketing aptitude, photography\/digital media ability and computer skills in order to support Lori\u2019s efforts to meet client needs.<\/p>\n<p>Besides real estate, Lori treasures time to grow in her faith, share her knowledge about alternative health, and spend time with family and friends. Outdoor activities such as biking, kayaking, hiking, hunting and wildlife management work are also high on her list for enjoyment.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Office: <\/strong>512.342.1800<br><strong>Email:<\/strong> <a href=\"mailto:l.mcfadden@horizonrealty.com\">l.mcfadden@horizonrealty.com<\/a><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ac11626 elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"ac11626\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<style>\n.elementor-column.elementor-col-33 ul.elementor-icon-list-items {\n    padding-bottom: 10px;\n}    \n<\/style>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Our Agents Lori McFadden Sales Associate Contact Lori was first licensed as a real estate agent in Sacramento, California in 1990, where she worked the residential market for